fields.title: Single Valued Data Types
fields.content: In Python, "single value data types" refer to data types that represent a single, atomic piece of information, as opposed to collection types that hold multiple values.

fields.title: Multi Valued or Collection Data Types
fields.content: Python provides several built-in collection data types for storing and organizing multiple items. The four primary collection types are: tuple, list, set and dictionary.

fields.title: What Is Python?
fields.content: Python is a high-level, versatile programming language known for its readability and ease of use. It's widely used in web development, data science, machine learning, and more, due to its clear syntax and extensive libraries. Python is interpreted, object-oriented, and dynamically typed, allowing for rapid development and flexibility.

fields.title: Indexing
fields.content: In Python, indexing refers to the method of accessing individual elements within a sequence by their position or numerical index.

fields.title: Slicing
fields.content: Slicing in Python is a powerful and flexible method for extracting specific portions (subsequences) from sequence types such as strings, lists, and tuples. It allows you to create new sequences based on a range of elements from an existing one, without modifying the original.
